        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="11">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, chock the wheels and turn the engine off.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <warning>
                    <para>Allow the engine to cool down before removing the pressure cap from the deaeration tank.
                        Always insulate the cap by wrapping it with a thick, heavy cloth. To avoid possible injury from
                        scalding coolant or steam, do not pull the pressure cap off immediately when it has been
                        loosened to the first notch. Pause momentarily to allow time for excess pressure to release
                        through the overflow tube.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The following Steps are for All Models Except Where Noted</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the radiator into a suitable clean container for reuse.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect hoses from the surge tank.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect harness connector from the low coolant sensor (Figure 1).</para>
                <figure id="f049021" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0490201.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Disconnect Sensor Harness (9900i Model Shown)</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the coolant sensor and save for reuse in new surge tank.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove surge tank mounting bolts (Figure 2).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049022" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0490202.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Removing Mounting Bolts (9900i Model Shown)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">9000 Models:</emph>
                    Loosen the surge tank mounting bracket (Figure 3).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049023" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0490203.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Loosen Bracket Bolts (9900i Model Shown)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the surge tank.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the low coolant sensor into the new surge tank (Figure 4).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049024" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0490204.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Install Sensor to New Surge Tank (9900i Model Shown)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the new surge tank with the bolts removed previously (Figure 5) and tighten the
                    mounting bracket bolts to 21 to 24 Lbf-ft (29 to 32 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049025" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0490205.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Mount New Surge Tank (9900i Model Shown)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the 1 inch I.D. hose to the bottom nipple on the surge tank.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">9000 Models:</emph>
                    Reconnect the 3/8 inch I.D. hose from the engine thermostat housing to the lower nipple on the surge
                    tank (Figure 7).
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">7600/8600 Models:</emph>
                    Remove the hose and elbow fitting at the engine thermostat housing and install new elbow fitting,
                    Part Number 864457R1. Tighten to 23 to 28 Lbf-ft (31 to 37 Nm). Install hose, Part Number 2643505R1
                    14 inches long, with hose clamp, Part Number 3591069C1. Attach the other hose end to the 1/2 inch
                    nipple on the surge tank with a hose clamp (Figure 6).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049026" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0490206.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="280px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Attach Hose with Clamps (7600 Model Shown)</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f049027" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0490207.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="280px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Reconnect Hose (9900i Model Shown)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the radiator 3/8 inch I.D.overflow hose and replace with Part number 2643504R1
                    (3/8 inch I.D X 43 inches long). Install the conduit from the old hose. Refer to Figure 9 for
                    conduit location on the hose.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">9000 Models:</emph>
                    Turn the hose "P" clip 180 degrees and route the hose through the "P" clip and connect it to the
                    surge tank (Figure 8).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049028" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0490208.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. "P" Clip Turned 180&#176; (9900i Model Shown)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">9000 Models:</emph>
                    Cable strap the overflow hose to the CAC (charge air cooler) pipe with cable straps and cable swivel
                    guide as shown in Figure 9.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">7600/8600 Models:</emph>
                    Cable strap the thermostat hose to surge tank hose as shown in Figure 10.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049029" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0490209.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Cable Strap Hose to CAC Pipe (9900i Model Shown)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Cable Lock Strap, Part Number 289802C1</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Cable Swivel Guide, Part Number 3554554C1</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Cable Lock Strap, Part Number 306132C1</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0490210" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0490210.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="264px"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Cable Strap Hoses (7600 Model Shown)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the overflow hose to the top nipple on the new surge tank (Figure 11).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0490211" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0490211.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="264px"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Connect the Overflow Hose (9900i Model shown)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refill the radiator.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
